    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-02T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-02T04:00:00-05:00" n="278"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11–248: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-02T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 2, 1948—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 2—8:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2065. Admiral Badger is preparing cable CNO regarding action contemplated under
                    revised directive Deptel 1505, October 27<note n="50" xml:id="d278fn50">See
                        footnote 46, <ref target="#pg_331">p. 331</ref>.</note> which closely
                    parallels third alternative our 1871, October 8, 3 p.m. He is urging dependents
                    depart but feels repercussions locally from ordered evacuation dependents would
                    have harmful effect outweighing beneficial evacuation all dependents. He
                    expressed to Minister-Counselor complete confidence his ability evacuate on
                    short notice Navy dependents as well as all Americans Tsingtao without in any
                    way affecting his ability handle any emergency evacuation situation arising
                    North China.</p>
                <p>Danger point [would be?] should Communists fail to heed his protestations of
                    neutrality, demand his immediate evacuation and endeavor overrun his
                    installations. Under such circumstances Badger, quite rightly we believe,
                    refuses to commit himself in advance as to action he would take. Such action, he
                    says, would depend on circumstances.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
